author: Pitchfork
title: Gunshot Fired in Migos and Sean Kingston Fight, Man Arrested
text:
Gunshot Fired in Migos and Sean Kingston Fight, Man Arrested Police confirm no one was injured in Vegas altercation Migos Migos perform in Las Vegas; photo by David Becker/Getty Images 
A man was arrested Tuesday for firing a gun during a fight between Migos and Sean Kingston in Las Vegas, police told the Associated Press . Mioses Johnson was detained by security guards before he was arrested. He was held in county jail on charges of felony assault with a weapon and carrying a firearm without a permit. The gunshot was fired in the air outside the Sands Expo & Convention Center, where a physical confrontation broke out following an argument between Migos and Kingston, officer Danny Cordero said. No one was injured, and Migos and Kingston were not named as suspects in the case. Kingston shared a video claiming that he wasn’t jumped by Migos. 
Pitchfork has reached out to Migos’ representatives for comment.
